			The word “Syntax”
			-----------------

			*Syntax* is a word we use to talk about “the correct way to write something”. If you write something incorrectly, you will have a “syntax error”. Here are some common pieces of syntax:

			- ; - Semicolon - This comes at the end of every statement in our code.
			- ( ) - Parentheses. These are used when we write functions or certain kinds of statements (like if-else and loops)
			- [ ] - Square Brackets (or just Brackets) - These are used when talking about Arrays.
			- { } - Curly Braces. These are used to talk about a piece of code. They usually mean something like “This piece of code is part of this function”.

