			Including Libraries
			-------------------

			You can use `#include<>` to get code from *libraries* by including their *Header File* (.h). These libraries may have functions that can help you. Here are some good ones:

			- `stdlib.h` - Standard Library. This has some basic functions, and is usually a good idea to include.
			- `stdio.h` - Standard Input/Output. This has functions for normal I/O and File I/O.
			- `string.h` - Every function involving strings is in here.
			- `math.h` - Useful math functions. This also has the Random number functions rand() and srand()
			- `time.h` - Useful functions that deal with time.

			You can also include your own header files, like this:

				#include”mycode.h”


	%section
